t%20of%20Commerce%20says%20the%20combined%20goods%20and%20services%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bea.gov%2Fnews%2F2025%2Fus-international-trade-goods-and-services-december-and-annual-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrade%20deficit%3C%2Fa%3E%20stretched%20to%20a%20gargantuan%20%24918.4%20billion%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%2017%25%20increase%20compared%20to%202023%2C%20although%20it's%20a%20little%20smaller%20than%202022's%20record-high%20of%20%24944.8%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETackling%20trade%20imbalances%20will%20likely%20be%20a%20key%20part%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump%C2%A0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E's%20second-term%20agenda.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20president's%20first%20official%20acts%20was%20to%20sign%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fpresidential-actions%2F2025%2F01%2Famerica-first-trade-policy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20executive%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%20calling%20for%20an%20%26quot%3BAmerica%20First%20Trade%20Policy%2C%26quot%3B%20emphasizing%20economic%20investment%20and%20reducing%20the%20trade%20deficit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FZRrKv%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22US%20trade%20balance%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22482%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20why%20the%20trade%20deficit%20is%20important%20and%20the%20role%20Trump's%20tariffs%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ad04f481-f3a5-4c3f-949a-f24855ffdf89%5C%22%3EA%20trade%20imbalance%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20trade%20deficit%20occurs%20when%20a%20country%20imports%20more%20than%20it%20exports%2C%20which%20has%20been%20the%20case%20in%20the%20United%20States%20for%20decades.%20The%20United%20States%20hasn't%20had%20a%20trade%20surplus%20since%201975%20%E2%80%94%20exactly%2050%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20trade%20deficit%20on%20goods%20alone%20was%20a%20record%20%241.2%20trillion%20in%202024%2C%20and%20there%20was%20a%20trade%20surplus%20on%20services%20of%20about%20%24293%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrade%20deficits%20can%20benefit%20the%20economy%20by%20allowing%20countries%20to%20consume%20more%20products%20than%20they%20produce.%20Trade%20deficits%20that%20are%20too%20big%2C%20however%2C%20can%20hurt%20domestic%20companies%20by%20potentially%20driving%20increased%20competition%20for%20less%20expensive%20foreign%20imports.%20Large%20trade%20deficits%20can%20also%20potentially%20lower%20a%20country's%20gross%20domestic%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strength%20of%20the%20US%20dollar%20means%20imports%20are%20slightly%20cheaper%20for%20American%20consumers%2C%20which%20is%20good.%20But%20it%20also%20means%20exports%20are%20more%20costly%20for%20non-US%20consumers.%20That%20can%20make%20it%20more%20difficult%20for%20US%20exporters%20to%20sell%20their%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22879983ec-16db-4ab0-8c3d-461bfa52ccb6%5C%22%3EHow%20Trump%20plans%20to%20balance%20the%20trade%20deficit%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20persistent%20trade%20deficit%20is%20something%20Trump%20has%20long%20sought%20to%20reverse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20Trump%20took%20office%2C%20he%20suggested%20a%20universal%2010%25%20to%2020%25%20tariff%20on%20every%20country%20to%20%E2%80%94%20among%20other%20things%20%E2%80%94%20reduce%20the%20number%20of%20foreign%20imports%20and%20bring%20down%20the%20trade%20deficit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225621%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22President%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20Japanese%20Prime%20Minister%20Shigeru%20Ishiba%20at%20the%20White%20House.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67a7b30d7bb3f854015c4966%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223747%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20Japanese%20Prime%20Minister%20Shigeru%20Ishiba%20discuss%20trade%20policy%20at%20the%20White%20House.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FAlex%20Brandon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20Trump%20said%20he'd%20announce%20%26quot%3Breciprocal%26quot%3B%20tariffs%20on%20multiple%20countries%20in%20the%20coming%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20Friday%20meeting%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Shigeru%20Ishiba%20of%20Japan%20at%20the%20White%20House%2C%20Trump%20said%20he%20wanted%20to%20cut%20the%20US%20trade%20deficit%20with%20Japan%2C%20which%20in%202024%20hit%20%2468.5%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20didn't%20rule%20out%20future%20tariffs%20for%20Japan.%20However%2C%20Ishiba%20was%20highly%20complimentary%20of%20the%20US%20president%20during%20their%20meeting%2C%20and%20Trump%20said%20he%20didn't%20believe%20Japan%20and%20the%20US%20would%20%26quot%3Bhave%20any%20problem%20whatsoever.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20levied%2025%25%20tariffs%20on%20Canada%20and%20Mexico%20and%2010%25%20tariffs%20on%20China%20earlier%20this%20month.%20Mexico%20and%20Canada%20have%20since%20struck%20deals%20with%20the%20Trump%20administration%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-2nd-term-calendar-deadlines-key-dates-timeline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epause%20the%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20at%20least%20early%20March.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20responded%20with%20its%20own%2010%25%20tariff%20on%20select%20US%20imports%20%E2%80%94%20including%20crude%20oil%2C%20agricultural%20machinery%2C%20and%20pickup%20trucks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20Trump's%20rationale%20for%20tariffs%20was%20his%20frustration%20with%20illegal%20immigration%20and%20border%20security%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20flow%20of%20illicit%20drugs%20into%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20also%20cited%20the%20elevated%20trade%20deficit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20have%20to%20balance%20out%20their%20trade%2C%20No.%201%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20reporters%20at%20Maryland's%20Joint%20Base%20Andrews%2C%20%3Cstrong%3Ereferring%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20to%20how%20Canada%20and%20Mexico%20could%20avoid%20tariffs.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20deficits%20with%20almost%20every%20country%20%E2%80%94%20not%20every%20country%2C%20but%20almost%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we're%20going%20to%20change%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20the%20US%20trade%20deficit%20with%20China%20was%20%24295%20billion%2C%20a%20major%20decline%20from%20the%20record%20%24418%20billion%20gap%20set%20in%202018%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0during%20Trump's%20first%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trade%20deficit%20with%20Mexico%2C%20however%2C%20grew%20from%20%2478%20billion%20in%202018%20to%20about%20%24172%20billion%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20States%20had%20a%20%2463%20billion%20trade%20deficit%20with%20Canada%20last%20year%2C%20but%20if%20oil%20and%20gas%20are%20left%20out%20of%20the%20equation%2C%20the%20United%20States%20would%20have%20a%20%2430%20billion%20trade%20surplus%20with%20its%20northern%20neighbor%2C%20according%20to%20MarketWatch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-trade-deficit-exports-imports-tariffs-us-consumers-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739050995000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67a3dbaa7bb3f854015bea7b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-trade-deficit-exports-imports-tariffs-us-consumers-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22President%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20made%20reducing%20the%20trade%20deficit%20a%20central%20part%20of%20his%20%26quot%3BAmerican%20First%20Trade%20Policy.%26quot%3B%20Here's%20what%20you%20need%20to%20know.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(John%20L.%20Dorman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A172%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%