be%20further%20tweaked%20by%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20this%20president%20can%20say%2C%20I%20refuse%20to%20spend%20money%20the%20way%20it%20was%20appropriated%2C%20why%20would%20any%20bipartisan%20group%20of%20senators%20be%20able%20to%20come%20to%20and%20keep%20an%20appropriations%20deal%20going%20forward%3F%26quot%3B%20Democratic%20Sen.%20Chris%20Coons%20of%20Delaware%20told%20reporters%20this%20week.%20%26quot%3BI%20get%20it%2C%20there's%20some%20disagreement%20about%20USAID%2C%20but%20the%20much%20more%20fundamental%20fight%20is%20over%20whether%20an%20agreement%20in%20appropriations%2C%20that%20is%20a%20law%2C%20will%20be%20respected.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Nixon-era%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-impoundment-trump-control-government-congress-spending-plan-doge-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EImpoundment%20Control%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20subsequent%20court%20cases%2C%20it's%20illegal%20for%20a%20president%20to%20simply%20refuse%20to%20spend%20congressionally%20approved%20funds.%20Trump%20and%20his%20allies%20have%20long%20signaled%20that%20they%20view%20that%20law%20as%20unconstitutional%20and%20will%20challenge%20it%20in%20the%20courts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHouse%20Minority%20Leader%20Hakeem%20Jeffries%20said%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20colleagues%20on%20Monday%20that%20Trump's%20recent%20spending%20moves%20%26quot%3Bmust%20be%20choked%20off%20in%20the%20upcoming%20government%20funding%20bill%2C%26quot%3B%20signaling%20a%20bid%20to%20use%20government%20funding%20as%20leverage%20to%20get%20Trump%20to%20change%20course.%20The%20following%20day%2C%20House%20Speaker%20Mike%20Johnson%20said%20that%20Jeffries%20had%20%26quot%3Blaid%20out%20the%20foundation%20for%20a%20government%20shutdown.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepublicans%20are%20generally%20seen%20as%20unable%20to%20pass%20a%20government%20funding%20bill%20on%20their%20own%20in%20the%20House%2C%20owing%20to%20their%20extremely%20slim%20majority%20and%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20hardline%20conservative%20bloc%20that's%20unwilling%20to%20pass%20bills%20that%20don't%20include%20extremely%20steep%20cuts.%20Even%20if%20that%20were%20possible%2C%20the%20Senate's%2060-vote%20%26quot%3Bfilibuster%26quot%3B%20rule%20means%20that%20Democratic%20cooperation%20is%20needed%20in%20the%20upper%20chamber.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Republicans%2C%20there's%20an%20expectation%20that%20Democrats%20will%20play%20ball%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20government%20funding%2C%20especially%20given%20Johnson's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmore-democrats-republicans-vote-government-shutdown-debt-ceilling-fourth-time-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrequent%20reliance%20on%20Democrats%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20pass%20funding%20bills%20in%20the%20last%20year%20or%20so.%20That's%20true%20even%20for%20the%20more%20Trump-skeptical%20in%20the%20GOP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20avoiding%20the%20cooperation%20that%20is%20required%2C%26quot%3B%20Republican%20Sen.%20Lisa%20Murkowski%20of%20Alaska%20told%20BI%2C%20adding%20that%20she%20believes%20Democrats'%20objections%20to%20Musk%20and%20funding%20freezes%20can%20be%20kept%20separate%20from%20the%20government%20funding%20fight.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20too%20important.%20We've%20got%20to%20get%20this%20done.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20among%20Democrats%2C%20there's%20a%20sense%20that%20their%20general%20willingness%20to%20fund%20the%20government%20has%20been%20taken%20for%20granted%20and%20that%20if%20there%20is%20a%20shutdown%2C%20it%20will%20be%20Republicans'%20to%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20up%20to%20the%20Republicans.%20They're%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20House%2C%20the%20Senate%2C%20and%20the%20White%20House%2C%26quot%3B%20Democratic%20Rep.%20Mark%20Pocan%20of%20Wisconsin%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20you%20know%2C%20if%20Morticia%20and%20Cousin%20Itt%20and%20Uncle%20Fester%20can%20all%20agree%20on%20something%2C%20then%20we%20won't%20have%20a%20shutdown.%20My%20guess%20is%20they're%20going%20to%20have%20some%20difficulty.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20no%20government%20funding%20bill%20is%20passed%20by%20March%2014%2C%20the%20federal%20government%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwill-government-shutdown-happen-elon-musk-doge-whats-at-stake-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erun%20out%20of%20funding%20and%20shut%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20aside%20from%20some%20essential%20functions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20federal%20workers%20would%20be%20at%20least%20temporarily%20out%20of%20work%2C%20airports%20would%20be%20delayed%2C%20national%20parks%20would%20be%20shuttered%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolitically%2C%20shutdowns%20tend%20to%20be%20painful%20for%20the%20party%20in%20power.%20The%20last%20time%20that%20the%20government%20shut%20down%20was%20in%20December%202018%2C%20when%20Trump's%20demand%20for%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20border%20wall%20funding%20was%20unable%20to%20pass%20Congress.%20At%2035%20days%2C%20it%20remains%20the%20longest%20shutdown%20in%20American%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-usaid-funding-government-shutdown-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739022367000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67a51180bfebcc4d029e1891%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-usaid-funding-government-shutdown-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Democrats%20say%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20moves%20to%20reshape%20the%20federal%20government%20without%20congressional%20input%20make%20reaching%20a%20deal%20nearly%20impossible.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bmetzger%40insider.com%20(Bryan%20Metzger)%22%2C%22engagement%22